        <p>You don't have to make an appointment to visit, come in today! Plan to spend 2-3 hours and follow the steps below to get the most of your time.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bring your career assessment results</strong> <br>
              Take the career assessment above so you have a better idea of what you want to do for work.
          </li>

            <li><strong>Complete and Sign the
                <a href="http://www.metrocareercenters.org/PDF/AJCC%20Membership%20Application%20fill%20in.pdf">Membership Application</a></strong></li>

            <li><strong>Read, Print and Sign the
              <a href="http://www.metrocareercenters.org/PDF/Lab%20Policies.pdf">Job Search Lab Policies</a></strong></li>

          <li><strong>Read, Print and Sign the
              <a href="http://www.metrocareercenters.org/PDF/Customer%20Suspension%20Policy.pdf">Customer Suspension Policy Form</a></strong></li>

          <li><strong>Sign up for a job seeker profile on <a href="https://www.caljobs.ca.gov/vosnet/Privacy/PrivacyAgreement.aspx?pu=False&rt=n&strAgreementLang=" target="_blank" title="CalJobs">CalJobs</a></strong><br>
              You can start looking for work immediately.
          </li>

            <li><strong>Create and Print a CalJobs resume
                <a href="http://www.metrocareercenters.org/PDF/AJCC%20Membership%20Application%20fill%20in.pdf">Membership Application</a></strong></li>


            <li><strong>Bring in two forms of identification.</strong><br>
              <a href="http://www.metrocareercenters.org/PDF/I-9%20Form.pdf">List of acceptable documents</a>
          </li>
